Package jumpingalien.model

Class World

  • java.lang.Object
    • jumpingalien.model.World
  • public class World
extends java.lang.Object
    A class of worlds which contain a player and other organisms, it also has a structure of tiles.

      • World

        @Raw
public World​(int tileSize,
             int nbTilesX,
             int nbTilesY,
             int[] targetTileCoordinate,
             int visibleWindowWidth,
             int visibleWindowHeight,
             int... geologicalFeatures)
      throws jumpingalien.util.ModelException
        Initialize a new world with give tileSize, number of tiles in the x direction, number of tiles in the x direction, number of tiles in the y direction, a coordinate for the target tile, the width of the visible window, the height of the visible window
        Parameters:
        tileSize - The size of a tile (number of pixels)
        nbTilesX - The number of tiles in each horizontal row
        nbTilesY - The number of tiles in each vertical column
        targetTileCoordinate - The coordinates of the target tile [pixelsX,pixelsY]
        visibleWindowWidth - The width of the visible window (number of pixels)
        visibleWindowHeight - The height of the visible window (number of pixels)
        geologicalFeatures - A list that defines the geological features of the tiles (in order), all integers 0 : AIR 1 : SOLID_GROUND 2 : WATER 3 : MAGMA 4 : ICE 5 : GAS Not specified : AIR
        Throws:
        jumpingalien.util.ModelException - TODO
